        "content": {
            "rendered": "<h3 class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b>Degrees</b></h3>\n<ul type=\"disc\">\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Ph.D. Vanderbilt University</li>\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">M.S. Sabanci University, Turkey</li>\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">B.A. Bogazici University, Turkey</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/halperarslan/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Personal Faculty Webpage</a></p>\n<h3 class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b>About</b></h3>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Dr. Arslan joined the Carlos Alvarez College of Business faculty in 2020. He holds a Ph.D. in economics from Vanderbilt University. He previously worked in the Department of Economics at Queenâ€™s University, Canada as a postdoctoral researcher. He teaches intermediate microeconomics and applied econometrics. He is a member of the American Economic Association, the Econometric Society and INFORMS.</p>\n<div>\n<h3 class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b>Research Interests</b></h3>\n</div>\n<ul type=\"disc\">\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Empirical industrial organization</li>\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Econometrics</li>\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Revenue management and pricing</li>\n<li class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Market design</li>\n</ul>\n<div>\n<h3 class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b>Selected Publications</b></h3>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">&#8220;Data-Driven Sports Ticket Pricing for Multiple Sales Channels with Heterogeneous Customers,&#8221; with Rob Easley, Ruxian Wang and Ovunc Yilmaz, <em>Manufacturing and Service Operations Management, </em>forthcoming.</p>\n</div>\n",
